      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for those suggestions. westlake sounds pretty good. i guess i'm a bit worried about the \"community feel\" part though... sometimes when places get too big or diverse it feels less stable or safe. do u think there's a correlation between the demographic makeup of a district and how \"safe\" and \"high-achieving\" it actually stays? like, should i be looking for districts that are more homogeneous to make sure the schools stay on top?",
